    JED class FES_Driver: Driver program for getting the free energy of two order parameters using 2D KDE This class imports bits/kde developed by Philip DeCamp.       • FES_Driver

        public FES_Driver(java.lang.String DVPs,
                  int op1,
                  int op2,

                  int offset,
                  double size,
                  java.lang.String dir,
                  java.lang.String out_dir,
                  java.lang.String descr)
        Class to create outputs for generating Free Energy Surfaces based on two order parameters.
        Parameters:
        DVPs: - The DVPs (PCs) from a JED PCA run
        op1: - The first order parameter (DVP1) (INT: the first column number)
        op2: - The Second order parameter (DVP2) (INT: the second column number)
        num_points: - The number of points (The number of data points that are to be extracted from the DVP to use for the KDE)
        offset: - The offset for reading points from the DVP (important if there are multiple runs combined)
        size: - The cellsize for the 2D grid in the KDE. Set to zero to determine automatically.
        dir: - The job input directory.
        out_dir: - The output directory.
        descr -
